Senator Oluremi Tinubu, wife of the national leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, has been ordained as an assistant pastor in the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) today, Tuesday 7th of August, 2018.
 
She was part of the new ministers ordained by the General Overseer of RCCG, Pastor Enoch Adejare, at the ongoing 65th annual convention currently holding at the church’s old auditorium in RCCG camp, Mowe, Ogun state.
 
Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, was also seen at the ordination ceremony greeting and talking with the General Overseer of RCCG, Pastor Enoch Adeboye.
 
Meanwhile, many have started congratulating the Tinubus over this new achievement.
 
“I congratulate your excellency, distinguished Senator Remi Tinubu OON, on your ordination as a Pastor in the RCCG. It is my prayer that Almighty God will continue to strengthen you as you serve the nation, humanity and his vineyard,” reads one of the massages on tweeter.
 
 
 
